description:
&lt;p&gt;The Northern Alliance Advanced Therapies Treatment Centre (NA-ATTC) has been successfully designated as one of three UK ATTCs. These centres have been tasked with optimising adoption of these new treatments into the NHS and to support the UK industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to employ a Project Manager to support the delivery of the NA-ATTC across Scotland and the North of England. Reporting to the Lead Project Manager, the successful candidate will take full responsibility for the day to day management of assigned work packages, working with clinical, industry, academic and research partners to deliver the Centre’s work programme to time and budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for self-motivated individuals with demonstrable project management experience who can apply their advanced organisational skills to manage conflicting demands on their time. These roles will involve coordination of management and work package-specific team meetings to ensure progress against objectives, development of detailed plans, supporting dissemination of materials and collaborative working with the wider project management team, providing support as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a flexible approach to work, the successful candidate will also have excellent communication skills and knowledge of terminology used in the advanced therapies sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
